WEBVTT

00:01.410 --> 00:04.290
♪ ♪

00:04.290 --> 00:06.380
Wow.

00:06.380 --> 00:09.550
PAUL DEVEREUX:
For 200 years archaeologists

00:09.550 --> 00:12.420
have been looking
at a silent movie,

00:12.420 --> 00:14.260
but suddenly
we've got a soundtrack.

00:14.260 --> 00:16.470
We're trying to get
the sensory information

00:16.470 --> 00:20.140
that was there when these people
built these places.

00:22.810 --> 00:24.810
And we're picking up
the 110 hertz,

00:24.810 --> 00:28.020
and it's vibrating
around this whole area.

00:28.020 --> 00:29.980
‐You can actually feel it
in your body. ‐Yes.

00:29.980 --> 00:32.740
That's quite amazing, actually.

00:32.740 --> 00:35.740
‐(horn blows) ‐GIORGIO
TSOUKALOS: Many ancient cultures

00:35.740 --> 00:38.660
around the world
worshipped sound.

00:38.660 --> 00:41.620
Is it possible that sound

00:41.620 --> 00:43.580
has this incredible power

00:43.580 --> 00:46.670
with which you could
do certain things?

00:46.670 --> 00:48.840
DAVID CHILDRESS:
Is there some grand design

00:48.840 --> 00:50.300
from extraterrestrials

00:50.300 --> 00:53.220
that was harmonically tuning

00:53.220 --> 00:55.970
all of these sites on Earth?

00:55.970 --> 00:59.510
DAVID WILCOCK: Extraterrestrials
are giving us clues

00:59.510 --> 01:02.140
that frequency
plays a much greater role

01:02.140 --> 01:05.810
in understanding matter,
energy, and consciousness

01:05.810 --> 01:08.770
than we allow for in our current
scientific paradigms.

01:08.770 --> 01:10.690
♪ ♪

01:39.760 --> 01:42.810
NARRATOR:
Baalbek, Lebanon.

01:42.810 --> 01:46.480
The 9,000‐year‐old
Temple of Jupiter

01:46.480 --> 01:49.020
contains three of the largest

01:49.020 --> 01:51.400
monolithic stones in the world,

01:51.400 --> 01:54.860
weighing approximately
1,000 tons‐‐

01:54.860 --> 01:57.990
or two million pounds‐‐ each.

01:57.990 --> 02:01.950
Puma Punku, Bolivia.

02:01.950 --> 02:05.040
Scattered across
a high desert plateau

02:05.040 --> 02:08.290
are precisely‐cut
100‐ton blocks,

02:08.290 --> 02:10.750
believed to date back

02:10.750 --> 02:15.460
at least 2,000 years,
and perhaps much earlier.

02:17.630 --> 02:20.640
The Giza Plateau, Egypt.

02:20.640 --> 02:22.760
The Great Pyramid is built

02:22.760 --> 02:26.600
from more than 2.3 million
limestone bricks,

02:26.600 --> 02:31.150
each weighing a staggering
5,000 pounds.

02:31.150 --> 02:35.530
All around the world
stand colossal monuments

02:35.530 --> 02:38.650
to mankind's ancient past;

02:38.650 --> 02:43.530
gigantic structures that have
endured for thousands of years,

02:43.530 --> 02:46.500
built with stone blocks
so massive

02:46.500 --> 02:49.040
that modern builders
have not even attempted

02:49.040 --> 02:50.920
to duplicate them.

03:00.470 --> 03:02.220
STEPHEN VANDER HART:
Our 988 Cat Loader

03:02.220 --> 03:04.390
can probably lift
a 22‐ton boulder,

03:04.390 --> 03:06.180
just for perspective.

03:06.180 --> 03:09.390
And it can probably roll
and drag along the ground,

03:09.390 --> 03:11.730
uh, maybe a 40‐ton boulder.

03:11.730 --> 03:15.230
But when you're talking
a 50‐ton boulder,

03:15.230 --> 03:19.440
then we would need to bring in
cranes, hydraulic jacks,

03:19.440 --> 03:20.990
steel beams, girders.

03:20.990 --> 03:22.490
It's a whole nother
set of tools,

03:22.490 --> 03:24.570
even with modern‐day technology.

03:24.570 --> 03:26.280
I mean, I can only imagine

03:26.280 --> 03:28.620
how they would move
boulders that size.

03:28.620 --> 03:30.460
It baffles my mind.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.790
I have no idea.

03:31.790 --> 03:33.130
It's crazy to think about.

03:35.090 --> 03:37.670
TSOUKALOS: How is it possible
that 10,000 years ago

03:37.670 --> 03:41.800
our ancestors moved around
the most massive of stones?

03:41.800 --> 03:43.590
Well, the answer is either

03:43.590 --> 03:45.510
another previous
super civilization

03:45.510 --> 03:47.510
existed here on Earth,

03:47.510 --> 03:53.560
or extraterrestrials imparting
technological knowledge to us.

03:53.560 --> 03:57.190
NARRATOR: Ancient astronaut
theorists suggest

03:57.190 --> 04:00.110
such structures
provide physical evidence

04:00.110 --> 04:03.570
that extraterrestrial beings
visited Earth

04:03.570 --> 04:07.030
and assisted our ancestors
in the distant past.

04:07.030 --> 04:10.120
And each of these
three megalithic sites,

04:10.120 --> 04:12.460
as well as numerous others,

04:12.460 --> 04:15.290
have very specific stories
behind them

04:15.290 --> 04:18.000
that say they were built,
not by men,

04:18.000 --> 04:23.300
but by the gods,
using the power of levitation.

04:23.300 --> 04:27.600
Some ancient mythologies
speak of the fact

04:27.600 --> 04:32.350
that some of these stones
were put into place with sound;

04:32.350 --> 04:37.610
that these things all of
a sudden levitated into place.

04:37.610 --> 04:42.530
What the local legend
of Stonehenge talks about

04:42.530 --> 04:44.740
is that those big stones

04:44.740 --> 04:48.830
were transported
by way of levitation.

04:50.790 --> 04:53.660
NARRATOR: Similar to the
mythical story of Stonehenge,

04:53.660 --> 04:57.670
the ancient legends
of Bolivia say that

04:57.670 --> 05:02.130
the megalithic stones of Puma
Punku were floated into place.

05:02.130 --> 05:05.260
In the fifth century BC,

05:05.260 --> 05:08.350
the Greek historian Herodotus
wrote that

05:08.350 --> 05:10.140
the Egyptians
were given knowledge

05:10.140 --> 05:12.060
from the guardians of the sky

05:12.060 --> 05:15.310
on how to float
the massive limestone blocks

05:15.310 --> 05:18.360
with which they built
the Great Pyramid.

05:18.360 --> 05:21.650
WILCOCK: What we see is
the very real possibility

05:21.650 --> 05:23.780
that extraterrestrial
civilizations visited Earth

05:23.780 --> 05:25.900
all throughout the world.

05:25.900 --> 05:29.280
And that each time they did,
they felt it was very important

05:29.280 --> 05:31.580
to impart this sacred knowledge

05:31.580 --> 05:35.370
about the importance
of acoustic frequencies

05:35.370 --> 05:39.380
in the keys to unlocking
the mysteries of the universe.

05:39.380 --> 05:43.800
NARRATOR: The University
of Bristol, England.

05:43.800 --> 05:48.050
January 17, 2017.

05:48.050 --> 05:51.760
Researchers unveil a prototype

05:51.760 --> 05:54.520
for what they call
a "portable tractor beam,"

05:54.520 --> 05:59.190
a handheld device
that can levitate small objects

05:59.190 --> 06:01.150
using only sound waves.

06:05.110 --> 06:07.070
JASON MARTELL: Recently
the University of Bristol

06:07.070 --> 06:10.870
came up with a handheld device
with an array of speakers

06:10.870 --> 06:14.790
that allows the holder of this
to actually focus sound waves,

06:14.790 --> 06:16.450
and sound waves alone,

06:16.450 --> 06:21.380
and then levitate small pieces
of light material.

06:23.380 --> 06:25.380
So when we look at this
portable tractor beam,

06:25.380 --> 06:27.260
can we extrapolate the idea

06:27.260 --> 06:29.890
that this is a technology
in its infancy,

06:29.890 --> 06:32.930
where in ancient times
it was actually being used

06:32.930 --> 06:34.930
to levitate large stones?

06:34.930 --> 06:38.890
NARRATOR:
At Johns Hopkins University,

06:38.890 --> 06:40.980
biomedical engineers

06:40.980 --> 06:42.730
have manipulated
ultrasound frequencies

06:42.730 --> 06:45.360
‐(steady beeping)
‐to deliver specialized drugs

06:45.360 --> 06:50.860
to specific parts in the
brain with surgical precision.

06:50.860 --> 06:53.280
And mathematicians
at Cardiff University

06:53.280 --> 06:54.870
have developed a method

06:54.870 --> 06:58.200
to literally stop a tsunami
in its tracks

06:58.200 --> 06:59.750
using acoustic waves.

06:59.750 --> 07:03.590
(waves crash, then stop)

07:03.590 --> 07:05.590
But while physicists are excited

07:05.590 --> 07:08.630
at the prospect
of using sound frequencies

07:08.630 --> 07:11.970
to levitate
and manipulate matter,

07:11.970 --> 07:14.260
they insist it is only
the beginning

07:14.260 --> 07:18.600
of a wave of cutting‐edge
acoustic technology.

07:18.600 --> 07:22.690
Could these amazing new
scientific breakthroughs

07:22.690 --> 07:25.770
simply be the first steps
in replicating

07:25.770 --> 07:28.360
what our ancestors
had been taught to harness

07:28.360 --> 07:32.450
thousands of years ago?

07:32.450 --> 07:34.070
WILCOCK: What if these
scientific experiments

07:34.070 --> 07:35.870
that we're looking at
are leading us

07:35.870 --> 07:38.580
to a much greater surprise,

07:38.580 --> 07:42.000
which is that sound
can be followed through

07:42.000 --> 07:44.420
to much greater levels
of efficiency

07:44.420 --> 07:47.880
in its usefulness
for all sorts of things

07:47.880 --> 07:50.510
that seem to be impossible?

07:50.510 --> 07:54.970
We may be just seeing now the
very first steps in our society

07:54.970 --> 07:57.560
of a robust technology

07:57.560 --> 08:00.430
that extraterrestrial
intelligent civilizations

08:00.430 --> 08:02.810
have long since
developed and perfected.

08:06.900 --> 08:09.360
NARRATOR:
Vancouver, Canada.

08:09.360 --> 08:12.950
February 17, 2012.

08:12.950 --> 08:15.370
At a symposium for

08:15.370 --> 08:18.580
the American Association
for the Advancement of Science,

08:18.580 --> 08:21.580
researchers gather to unveil
the latest discoveries

08:21.580 --> 08:24.960
in the burgeoning field
of archaeoacoustics.

08:24.960 --> 08:28.170
LINDA ENEIX: Archaeoacoustics
is a new field of study,

08:28.170 --> 08:32.300
multi‐disciplinary, and we
are incorporating three facets:

08:32.300 --> 08:35.260
one would be archaeology,
anthropology,

08:35.260 --> 08:38.220
a second would be
sound and acoustics,

08:38.220 --> 08:40.640
the third would
be space and architecture.

08:43.230 --> 08:44.850
And all three of those areas

08:44.850 --> 08:47.730
are put together
to try to explore

08:47.730 --> 08:50.980
what was going on
with sound in ancient places.

08:50.980 --> 08:53.490
NARRATOR:
Recent tests at Stonehenge

08:53.490 --> 08:55.610
suggest that
the megalithic stones

08:55.610 --> 08:58.620
were positioned to cause sound
wave interference patterns,

08:58.620 --> 09:02.160
similar to noise‐cancelling
headphones,

09:02.160 --> 09:04.410
creating spots of total silence

09:04.410 --> 09:06.710
at various points
around the circle.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.250
Statues of divine beings

09:11.250 --> 09:13.760
in the 3,000‐year‐old
Chavín de Huántar

09:13.760 --> 09:16.050
ceremonial center in Peru

09:16.050 --> 09:18.470
project a feline‐like roar

09:18.470 --> 09:20.140
when ancient shell trumpets
are played nearby.

09:20.140 --> 09:22.060
(trumpeting)

09:22.060 --> 09:24.890
And at the Pyramid
of the Feathered Serpent

09:24.890 --> 09:26.980
in Chichen Itza, Mexico,

09:26.980 --> 09:30.650
sound echoes mimic
the cry of the quetzal...

09:30.650 --> 09:32.440
(clapping, bird chirp echoes)

09:32.440 --> 09:34.150
(quetzal chirping)

09:34.150 --> 09:36.650
...a bird the Mayans
believed was a messenger

09:36.650 --> 09:41.990
for their creator god Kukulkan.

09:41.990 --> 09:43.910
ENEIX:
People are coming forward now

09:43.910 --> 09:46.830
with these ideas that maybe
were considered pseudoscience

09:46.830 --> 09:48.830
for a long time.

09:48.830 --> 09:52.710
These days, it's beginning
to be taken seriously

09:52.710 --> 09:56.050
that sound belongs in the study
of the ancient world.

09:56.050 --> 09:58.760
TSOUKALOS:
Many ancient cultures

09:58.760 --> 10:02.510
around the world
worshipped sound

10:02.510 --> 10:06.100
because sound was deemed
to be divine in origin.

10:06.100 --> 10:09.600
(echoing trumpeting)

10:09.600 --> 10:13.440
Is it possible that
the reason why our ancestors

10:13.440 --> 10:17.700
talked about divine sound
is not necessarily because

10:17.700 --> 10:19.660
they were referring to music...

10:19.660 --> 10:21.870
(trumpeting)

10:21.870 --> 10:25.950
...but that sound has
this incredible power

10:25.950 --> 10:28.460
with which you could do
certain things...

10:28.460 --> 10:30.380
(sound stops)

10:30.380 --> 10:32.460
...but it's just that
we've lost this knowledge

10:32.460 --> 10:34.300
over the millennia?

10:34.300 --> 10:38.170
NARRATOR: According to
ancient astronaut theorists,

10:38.170 --> 10:40.590
there is evidence
that our ancestors

10:40.590 --> 10:42.930
utilized the power
of sound waves

10:42.930 --> 10:47.600
to accomplish amazing feats
that defied gravity.

10:47.600 --> 10:50.600
But might they have learned
of acoustic applications

10:50.600 --> 10:53.230
far more profound
than those involved

10:53.230 --> 10:55.530
in moving giant boulders?

10:55.530 --> 10:59.900
Perhaps further clues
can be found

10:59.900 --> 11:03.870
by examining some of ancient
man's most important structures;

11:03.870 --> 11:07.540
structures that weren't
built with sound,

11:07.540 --> 11:10.290
but built to make sound.

11:15.800 --> 11:18.380
NARRATOR:
Paola, Malta.

11:18.380 --> 11:20.930
Deep beneath this small town

11:20.930 --> 11:23.300
in the middle
of the Mediterranean Sea

11:23.300 --> 11:25.640
rests one of the oldest
subterranean structures

11:25.640 --> 11:27.640
in the world.

11:27.640 --> 11:30.890
ENEIX: On the islands of Malta,
there are prehistoric remains

11:30.890 --> 11:34.230
that are comprised
of megalithic underground sites,

11:34.230 --> 11:38.030
which were considered
to be communal burial sites.

11:38.030 --> 11:41.780
The most famous of these
is the Hal‐Saflieni Hypogeum.

11:41.780 --> 11:46.950
Hal‐Saflieni dates back
to about 6,000 years ago.

11:46.950 --> 11:49.290
ROBERT SCHOCH:
It's multilayered,

11:49.290 --> 11:51.830
three major levels,

11:51.830 --> 11:53.580
and it's really just astounding

11:53.580 --> 11:56.920
to have carved it
into the limestone.

11:56.920 --> 11:59.590
I'm a geologist.
I know how difficult it is

11:59.590 --> 12:02.680
to engineer something like that
and carry it out.

12:02.680 --> 12:07.010
To me, it shows
incredible sophistication

12:07.010 --> 12:10.770
on a technological basis.

12:10.770 --> 12:14.230
I can't claim that I know
exactly how they did it.

12:14.230 --> 12:17.360
NARRATOR:
When the Hal‐Saflieni Hypogeum

12:17.360 --> 12:20.440
was first discovered in 1902,

12:20.440 --> 12:23.610
archaeologists were astounded
to find buried within it

12:23.610 --> 12:27.080
more than 7,000 skeletons.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.450
In May 1920,

12:29.450 --> 12:32.410
a <i>National Geographic</i> article
reported

12:32.410 --> 12:34.670
that many of the remains
were those of humans

12:34.670 --> 12:36.670
that were "long‐skulled."

12:36.670 --> 12:39.340
But during World War II,

12:39.340 --> 12:42.010
the site was plundered
by vandals,

12:42.010 --> 12:45.890
and the skeletons
mysteriously disappeared.

12:45.890 --> 12:50.390
Luckily, 11 of the elongated
skulls were salvaged,

12:50.390 --> 12:54.850
and at least one of these
displays a non‐human feature‐‐

12:54.850 --> 12:58.150
it is missing the sagittal
suture that connects

12:58.150 --> 13:02.030
the parietal bones
on all human skulls.

13:02.030 --> 13:05.700
CHILDRESS:
A bizarre report came

13:05.700 --> 13:09.450
from a woman named Lois Jessop,

13:09.450 --> 13:12.410
who had worked for the British
Consulate in Malta.

13:12.410 --> 13:15.710
She had been visiting
the Hypogeum,

13:15.710 --> 13:18.250
and had convinced
one of the caretakers

13:18.250 --> 13:22.130
to let her go into
the lowest chamber.

13:22.130 --> 13:25.680
She claimed that she came out

13:25.680 --> 13:28.300
into a ledge in a great fissure

13:28.300 --> 13:31.100
that was beneath Malta.

13:31.100 --> 13:34.390
And on a ledge on the other side
of the fissure,

13:34.390 --> 13:38.900
she claimed she saw
very tall men.

13:38.900 --> 13:41.900
TSOUKALOS:
According to her account,

13:41.900 --> 13:46.740
she saw about 20 white‐haired
giants that looked up at her

13:46.740 --> 13:50.990
and motioned her to come down.

13:50.990 --> 13:55.710
One has to wonder if the
Hypogeum has some sort of

13:55.710 --> 13:57.460
an extraterrestrial presence.

13:59.960 --> 14:04.170
NARRATOR: As incredible as
Lois Jessop's story may be,

14:04.170 --> 14:07.550
perhaps the most extraordinary
discovery at the Hypogeum

14:07.550 --> 14:10.180
has to do with sound.

14:11.850 --> 14:14.770
In February of 2014,

14:14.770 --> 14:18.140
archaeoacoustics researcher
Linda Eneix

14:18.140 --> 14:23.230
gathered an assemblage of audio,
geology and archaeology experts

14:23.230 --> 14:27.200
to test the acoustic properties
of the most mysterious chamber

14:27.200 --> 14:30.570
in this site, known as
the Oracle Room.

14:31.990 --> 14:33.740
After extensive testing,

14:33.740 --> 14:35.200
Linda and her team reached

14:35.200 --> 14:37.210
an incredible conclusion.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.830
The entire Hypogeum resonates

14:40.830 --> 14:44.210
at the specific frequency
of 110 hertz.

14:46.800 --> 14:50.050
ENEIX: You physically feel
the vibration of that sound

14:50.050 --> 14:54.260
‐in your whole body.
‐(frequency humming)

14:54.260 --> 14:56.560
It was, uh, mesmerizing.

14:58.770 --> 15:02.400
The water in the body's tissue
responds to that,

15:02.400 --> 15:05.440
and your whole body tunes into
this vibration

15:05.440 --> 15:08.650
that's wrapping around you
in the sound.

15:08.650 --> 15:10.910
(gong resonates)

15:10.910 --> 15:14.240
NARRATOR: Sound is created by
the vibration of an object,

15:14.240 --> 15:18.410
which causes the air surrounding
it to vibrate and form a wave.

15:18.410 --> 15:20.710
MICHAEL DENNIN: Depending on the
frequency it oscillates with,

15:20.710 --> 15:23.790
that will determine the note
or the tone you hear.

15:23.790 --> 15:26.880
Hertz is the unit we use
to measure frequency.

15:26.880 --> 15:30.340
It's basically the number of
oscillations per second.

15:30.340 --> 15:34.350
Resonance is basically whenever
something is vibrating,

15:34.350 --> 15:37.270
that frequency matches the
natural frequency

15:37.270 --> 15:39.270
or vibration of the object.

15:39.270 --> 15:42.900
This is really important with
sound applications.

15:42.900 --> 15:46.980
If you take an enclosed space,
the way you get a resonance

15:46.980 --> 15:51.610
is to make the size of the room
or space match the frequencies

15:51.610 --> 15:54.570
and wavelength of the sound
you're trying to achieve.

15:54.570 --> 15:56.830
So that when it hits the ends
of the walls,

15:56.830 --> 15:58.870
it reflects just right.

15:58.870 --> 16:01.120
These reflections
build up the sound,

16:01.120 --> 16:04.170
or magnitude, of that vibration.

16:04.170 --> 16:06.090
CHILDRESS:
What is going on here,

16:06.090 --> 16:09.630
and why are they specifically
using that frequency?

16:09.630 --> 16:12.180
So, you have to wonder whether
extraterrestrials weren't

16:12.180 --> 16:16.010
involved in tuning the Hypogeum

16:16.010 --> 16:18.390
to create this special
frequency.

16:18.390 --> 16:21.100
NARRATOR:
Could the Hypogeum in Malta

16:21.100 --> 16:23.020
have been built upon
the instructions

16:23.020 --> 16:24.770
of extraterrestrials

16:24.770 --> 16:28.980
with a very specific
acoustic purpose in mind?

16:28.980 --> 16:33.780
If so, does the 110 hertz
frequency that it is tuned to

16:33.780 --> 16:36.200
hold some special power?

16:39.200 --> 16:41.950
County Meath, Ireland.

16:41.950 --> 16:43.290
DEVEREUX:
This is the entrance.

16:43.290 --> 16:44.580
TSOUKALOS:
Wow.

16:44.580 --> 16:47.130
NARRATOR:
In January of 2017,

16:47.130 --> 16:50.300
researcher and publisher
Giorgio Tsoukalos

16:50.300 --> 16:52.970
traveled to the Newgrange
passage tomb

16:52.970 --> 16:56.340
to meet with archaeoacoustics
expert Paul Devereux.

16:59.310 --> 17:03.100
Here in this
5,000‐year‐old tomb,

17:03.100 --> 17:05.350
and at dozens of other
ancient megalithic sites

17:05.350 --> 17:07.360
across the world,

17:07.360 --> 17:10.690
Paul has been studying the
effects of sound resonance.

17:12.610 --> 17:14.240
Wow.

17:14.240 --> 17:16.820
NARRATOR: Today,
he will be running a test

17:16.820 --> 17:19.030
to discover whether or not

17:19.030 --> 17:22.620
the Newgrange structure was
built with an acoustic purpose

17:22.620 --> 17:26.960
and made to resonate
at a specific frequency.

17:28.790 --> 17:30.550
(device beeps)

17:30.550 --> 17:33.590
DEVEREUX:
We sweep a sound wave

17:33.590 --> 17:36.130
through the chamber

17:36.130 --> 17:40.050
